==English==
===Verb===
'''[[close]] [[in]] [[on]]'''
#{{idiom}} To [[enclose]] [[around]]; to [[tighten]] or [[shrink]]; to [[collapse]].
#:''Sometimes it feels like the walls are '''closing in on''' me.''
#{{idiom}} To [[catch up]] with in a [[chase]]; to near the end of a [[pursuit]].
#:''The police '''closed in on''' the suspect.''
#{{idiom}} To near a [[goal]] or [[completion]].
#:''I think we are '''closing in on''' the end of this project.''